quest_title: The escape velocity from earth is \(v_{e} .\) A body is projected with velocity \(2v_{e} \) with what constant velocity will it move in the inter planetary space
explanation_txt:
Kinectic energy of the body at launch \(=\cfrac{1}{2}m(2v_{e})^{2}=2mv_{e}^{2}\)

Kinetic energy of the body left at inter planatory space = \(2mv_{e}^{2}-\cfrac{GMm}{R}=2mv_{e}^{2}-\cfrac{1}{2}mv_{e}^{2}=\cfrac{3}{2}mv_{e}^{2}=\cfrac{1}{2}m(\sqrt{3}v_{e})^{2}\)

\(\therefore\) Velocity of the body in space \(=\sqrt{3}v_{e}\)

\(\therefore \mathrm{F}^{\prime}=2 \mathrm{F}\)

quest_title: If \(\vec{a}\) is any vector, \( (\vec{a} \times \hat{\imath})^2 + (\vec{a} \times \hat{\jmath})^2 + (\vec{a} \times \hat{k})^2 \) is:
explanation_txt:
Let \( \vec{a} = (a_1,a_2,a_3) \)

\( \vec{a} \times \hat{\imath} = \begin{vmatrix} \hat{\imath} & \hat{\jmath} & \hat{k} \\ 1 & 0 & 0 \\ a_1 & a_2 & a_3 \end{vmatrix} \)

Expanding along second row,

\( \vec{a} \times \hat{\imath} = a_3 \hat{ \jmath} - a_2 \hat{k} \)

Squaring, \( (\vec{a} \times \hat{\imath})^2 = a_2^2+a_3^2 \)

Similarly,

\( (\vec{a} \times \hat{\jmath})^2 = a_1^2+a_3^2 \)

\( (\vec{a} \times \hat{k})^2 = a_1^2+a_2^2 \)

Ading all we get \(2a^2\)
